<p><b><center><span style="color:red"><font size="20">Agapanthus Postbloom</span></center></b><font size="16">It is a popular garden plant around the world, especially in Mediterranean climates.It is native of Natal and Cape of Good Hope in South Africa, local names include agapant, bloulelie, isicakathi and ubani. Most of the cultivated plants of the genus Agapanthus are hybrids or cultivars of this species.</p>
